warning[W04039]: unable to determine principal type for literal
  ┌─ tests/development/typing/signed_int_neg_unsigned_literal.move:7:19
  │
7 │         let _x = -1u8;
  │                   ^^^ Could not determine a concrete type for this signed numeric literal, so defaulting to 'i64'
  │
  = To avoid this warning, add an explicit type annotation, e.g., '<num>i64'
  = This warning can be suppressed with '#[allow(untyped_literal)]' applied to the 'module' or module member ('const', 'fun', or 'struct')

